#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:1
msgid "BPMN Modeler"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:3
msgid ""
"The BPMN Modeler is a full BPMN 2.0 process editor integrated into the "
"Linked Data Explorer. It lets you design government service workflows "
"visually, link `BusinessRuleTask` elements to DMN decision models or DRD "
"chains, link `UserTask` and `StartEvent` elements to Camunda Forms authored "
"in the Form Editor, and deploy the complete bundle — BPMN, subprocess BPMNs, "
"and forms — to Operaton in a single operation."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:12
msgid "Three-panel layout"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:14
msgid "The Modeler uses the same three-panel layout as the Chain Builder:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:16
msgid ""
"**Left panel** — Process list. Shows all saved processes with create, "
"rename, and delete actions. An EXAMPLE badge marks protected processes that "
"cannot be deleted."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:17
msgid ""
"**Centre panel** — Canvas. Interactive BPMN 2.0 canvas powered by bpmn-js, "
"with drag-and-drop palette, zoom controls, and scroll-to-zoom."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:18
msgid ""
"**Right panel** — Properties. Shows element type, ID, name field, and — for "
"`BusinessRuleTask` elements — the DMN/DRD decision reference section."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:22
msgid "Process library"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:24
msgid ""
"The left panel lists all processes grouped by their role in the AWB shell "
"pattern."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:26
msgid "Shell / subprocess hierarchy"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:28
msgid ""
"The Linked Data Explorer models government service workflows as two-layer "
"BPMN compositions: a universal **AWB shell** process handles the eight "
"statutory procedural phases, and a product-specific **subprocess** delivers "
"the substantive decision via a Call Activity. The process list reflects this "
"structure visually."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:30
msgid ""
"Shell processes are top-level entries. Their subprocesses are indented "
"beneath them with a tree connector. Standalone processes — those with no "
"parent-child relationship — appear as top-level entries without indentation."
msgstr ""

