msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:75
msgid ""
"The palette provides all standard BPMN 2.0 elements: start, intermediate, "
"and end events; tasks (including business rule tasks); gateways (exclusive, "
"parallel, inclusive, event-based); sub-processes; data objects; pools; and "
"text annotations."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:79
msgid "DMN/DRD linking"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:81
msgid ""
"When a `BusinessRuleTask` is selected in the properties panel, a **Link to "
"DMN/DRD** dropdown appears. It loads options from two sources simultaneously:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:83
msgid ""
"**DRDs (Unified Chains)** — DRD templates saved locally from the Chain "
"Builder"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:84
msgid ""
"**Single DMNs** — individual decision models from the active TriplyDB "
"endpoint"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:86
msgid ""
"Selecting an option auto-populates `camunda:decisionRef` with the correct "
"identifier and suggests a value for `camunda:resultVariable`. A visual info "
"card below the dropdown confirms the selection, with purple styling for DRDs "
"and blue for single DMNs. DRD cards also show the chain composition (which "
"DMNs the DRD combines)."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:90
msgid "Export"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:92
msgid ""
"Processes can be exported as `.bpmn` files for deployment to Operaton. The "
"XML uses `camunda:` namespace attributes, which Operaton accepts for "
"compatibility with the Camunda 7 ecosystem."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:96
msgid "Form linking"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:98
msgid ""
"When a `UserTask` or `StartEvent` is selected, the properties panel shows a "
"**Link to Form** dropdown in addition to the standard element fields. The "
"dropdown lists every form currently stored in the Form Editor's "
"`localStorage`."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:105
msgid "Selecting a form writes two attributes to the BPMN XML:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:107
msgid ""
"camunda:formRef=\"kapvergunning-start\"\n"
"camunda:formRefBinding=\"latest\""
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:112
msgid ""
"`camunda:formRefBinding=\"latest\"` instructs Operaton to always resolve the "
"most recently deployed version of that form ID, eliminating the need for "
"version pinning."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:114
msgid ""
"A **green badge** appears below the element on the canvas once a form is "
"linked, showing the form ID. The badge colour distinguishes form links "
"(green) from DMN decision links (blue)."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:116
msgid ""
"To remove a form link, open the **Link to Form** dropdown and select the "
"blank option at the top."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:120
msgid "Document template linking"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:122
msgid ""
"When a `UserTask` is selected, the properties panel shows a **Link decision "
"template** dropdown below the form selector. The dropdown lists every "
"document template saved in the Document Composer's `localStorage`."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cbpmn-modeler.md:129
msgid ""
"Selecting a template writes `camunda:documentRef` to the BPMN XML and "
"renders a **purple badge** (📄) beneath the element on the canvas. The badge "
"is positioned below the green form badge so all three linked artefacts are "
"visible simultaneously:"
msgstr ""

